    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Availability of adopted National Adaptation Plan (NAP) for the 5 key sectors (agriculture, water, health, housing and emergency management) and three target provinces of this project (Karakalpakstan, Bukhara and Khorezm).</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2020">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">Despite recent assessments and risk analyses that have been undertaken in identifying vulnerable regions and economic sectors to the effects of climate change, no framework exists to date on climate change adaptation, nor climate change at large</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.1 A participatory, inter-agency working group on adaptation set up
1.2 Preparation of framework on adaptation to climate change initiated
1.3 Capacities for adaptation planning in up to 10 institutions assessed, and staff trained
1.4 Barriers analyzed and recommendations made to inform and initiate framework on adaptation
1.5 Outreach and advocacy plans rolled out in 3 priority provinces
1.6 Climate and gender sensitive indicators developed and integrated into national database. 30-40 persons trained to report and update the database
1.7 Best practices consolidated and made publicly available
1.8 Existing information reviewed, compiled and complemented with additional assessment for the health sector
1.9 Economic analysis system strengthened to appraise adaptation options and stakeholders trained on their application
1.10 CCA priorities integrated into sectoral plans and &#x2018;open budget&#x2019;
1.11 Financing strategy developed, and additional sources of financing identified
1.12 Strategy to support private investments in place and consultations held</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.1 Composition of an Inter-Agency Working Group on climate change adaptation set and confirmed through official communication with the responsible government agencies based on the developed and proposed Terms of Reference for the IAWG. 
1.2 Climate Action Strategy for Uzbekistan until 2030 drafted by Uzhydromet and is under consideration by the Government to adopt. It includes a particular climate adaptation section, which indicates the most climate vulnerable sectors, and provides framework, based on which sectoral and regional NAP development can be built on by the project with support of Inter-Agency Working Group on climate change adaptation that is to be adopted by the government.
1.3 Capacities of 6 institutions: ministers of agriculture, water, health, construction, emergencies at sectoral level and ministry of finance at national level assessed and corresponding recommendations for training needs focused on adaptation planning formulated. Consolidated Capacity Gaps report, and Capacity Development Plan developed. Training programs on capacity building on adaptation to climate change at the national and regional levels focused on ensuring effective intersectoral interaction for adaptation planning are designed.
1.4 Barriers in the five key target sectors at national and regional levels analyzed. 
1.5 Communication Strategy for Uzhydromet developed
1.6 Gender sensitive indicators developed. Mechanism for integration of the gender sensitive indicators developed. 
1.7 Not started yet
1.8 Current status of the health sector reviewed, existing information collected and compiled. 
1.9 Economic analysis system to assess adaptation options initiated, including tools and methodology for economic analysis.
1.10 Not started yet
1.11 Not started yet
1.12 Not started yet</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
